💰HERE’S THE BREAKDOWN!💰 

➡️Fantasy Brown Quartzite in leathered finish for the kitchen and butler’s pantry, fabrication, and installation.
➡️Calacatta porcelain backsplash behind the stove and coffee bar, fabrication, and installation.
➡️Two embedded steel bars to support the island overhang.
➡️Outlet and pot filler cut outs.

The cost of countertops can vary WIDELY, so yes this is relative, but hopefully helpful!

1️⃣ I had decided my non-negotiables were a natural stone, preferably quartzite in a non reflective leathered finish.

➡️The stone we went with is leathered quartzite in FANTASY BROWN.

2️⃣ THE REMNANTS PILE!! We saved money by looking at what was available in this section of “leftovers” from other projects! I was pretty set on a white countertop, but when there was enough material of the Fantasy Brown available in the remnants pile (and my husband really loved it!), we took a sample home and thought on it for a few days before making the decision to change up our design.🙌🏻

3️⃣Our kitchen is on the smaller side. Our entire home is 1900 sq. ft.! Countertops included are the island, range and coffee bar area, as well as the butler’s pantry.

4️⃣The backsplash was installed behind the range and coffee bar, but nothing in the butler’s pantry. It was a one off porcelain piece drastically reduced and was just enough to be fabricated and installed for these spaces. We have lower ceilings which made this work!

➡️SAVE FOR LATER IF YOU FOUND THIS HELPFUL!⬅️
